    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Scalar functions can have performance implications, especially when used in SELECT statements that process large datasets. Each row processed by the query may invoke the function, leading to potential performance bottlenecks. It is important to ensure that the function is optimized and that its logic is as efficient as possible to minimize overhead."
